18. Best Practices

✅ Always create a PDB for production workloads.

✅ Use kubectl drain, not kubectl delete pod.

✅ Use at least 3 replicas for HA applications.

✅ Combine PDB with anti-affinity and topology spread constraints.

✅ Test node maintenance in a staging cluster before production.

19. CKA Exam Tips

Remember:

PDB protects only voluntary disruptions.
Deleting a Pod or Deployment directly bypasses the PDB.
kubectl drain respects the PDB through the Eviction API.
minAvailable and maxUnavailable are mutually exclusive in a PDB.
PDBs are commonly tested with Deployments and StatefulSets.
